<HEADLINE> Panel Discussions Open to Press </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Panel discussions of
delegates from two provinces and one municipality to the ongoing
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China opened to
the press today.
</P>
<P>
They were Guangdong and Fujian provinces and Chongqing
Municipality, the fourth or the newly designated municipality in
China.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from Guangdong said that they are determined to rally
closely around the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
Lu Ruihua, governor of Guangdong, told 100-plus Chinese and
overseas reporters that the achievements Guangdong has made since
the start of the economic reforms in the late 1970s were the fruit
of implementing Deng Xiaoping Theory and emancipating the mind.
</P>
<P>
The gross domestic product of Guangdong has soared to 650
billion yuan since last National Party Congress. Its industrial
output value increased at an average annual rate of 30 percent, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Chen Mingyi from the southeast coastal province of Fujian said
Fujian shoulders a heavier responsibility in realizing peaceful
reunification of the motherland as it faces Taiwan. It will
increase its cooperation with Taiwan so as to help promote the
peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Outlining major tasks for Chongqing's future development, Zhang
Delin, secretary of the Chongqing Municipal Party Committee, said
the city government will reinforce its economic strength, improve
its urban functions and boost its vast rural economic development,
and complete the task of resettling one million people for the
sake of the construction of the Three Gorges Project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
