<HEADLINE> Third Generation of Party Leadership "Strong," Say Delegates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The remarkable progress China
has made in the past five years has proved that the third
generation of the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin as the
core is a strong and outstanding leading collective.
</P>
<P>
This is a view shared by many delegates at the on-going 15th
National Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
China has achieved rapid economic development over the recent
five years. It is exceptional in the world to have achieved "soft
landing" of the national economy while successfully curbing
inflation, said Li Zhijian, a Standing Committee member of the
Beijing Municipal Party Committee.
</P>
<P>
The facts have proven that the third generation leadership with
Jiang Zemin as the core has judged China's current situation based
on China's reality. What merits special attention is that the
leadership has specially emphasized that the greatest reality in
China is that the country has been and will be in the primary
stage of socialism in a considerably long period of time, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Sixian, head of Xuhui District, Shanghai, commented that
the Party Central Committee has established an excellent image in
the international community with distinctive characteristics and
the collective leadership has handled well the relations between
reform, development and stability.
</P>
<P>
Ma Sizhong, provincial governor of central China's Henan
Province, said the fact in which the Party Central Committee has
steadily improved the material and cultural life of the people
over the past five years proves the leadership has full capability
to promote China's reform and opening up and socialist
construction to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from Shanghai's Pudong New Area said by citing many
convincing facts from Pudong's development to support the point.
Over the past five years, Pudong's GDP has grown from 10
billion yuan in 1992 to 51 billion yuan in 1996, according to a
delegate from the booming Shanghai area.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from east China's provinces of Jiangsu and Shandong
also spoke highly of the achievements scored in their respective
provinces. They owe the achievements to holding high the great
banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory and the strong leadership of the
Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin as the core.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
