<HEADLINE> No England Team for Rugby, Cricket at Commonwealth Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 14 (Xinhua) -- England will not sent
players to the rugby and cricket competitions at next year's
Commonwealth Games in Kuala Lumpur, officials said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Commonwealth Games Federation (CGF) chairman Michael Fennel
said that it was a disappointment that England's absence from the
two sports.
</P>
<P>
"While we are extremely disappointed with England's absence in
cricket and rugby, we have to respect their decision," Fennel told
the Sunday Star, after releasing the entries for the two events.
</P>
<P>
England were reported to have made an eleventh hour attempt to
get their professional clubs to release their players but it was
in vain.
</P>
<P>
Scotland and Northern Ireland would also not participate in
rugby but world champions South Africa, New Zealand and Australia
have confirmed their entries.
</P>
<P>
Sevens rugby, cricket, netball and hockey will all make their
Commonwealth Games debut in Kuala Lumpur. 
</P>
</TEXT>
