<HEADLINE> China Finishes 1-2 at Women's World Cup Table Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Wang Ju beat Li Nan 3-2 in
an all-Chinese final to give the host country a top-two finish at
the women's world cup table tennis tournament which ended here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Wang Nan rallied from 7-14 behind and clinched the fifth and
fatal set in 21-17. The two split the first four sets as Wang
took the first and fourth in 21-15, 21-16 while Li Nan won the
second and third set in 21-17 and 23-21.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion and Olympic gold medalist Deng Yaping of
China quit the three-day competition with back and knee injuries.
</P>
</TEXT>
