<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Somali Factions Criticized for Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU,September 14 (xinhua)-- A local human rights
organization has today strongly criticized the Somali faction
leaders and their administration for being responsible about the
current high crime rate.
</P>
<P>
In a two page communique issued today, the North Mogadishu
based human rights organization, Dr Ismail Jumale Human Rights
Center, criticized the faction leaders for their failure to cope
with the increasing insecurity in the Somali capital which
brought about abductions, killings and torture against innocent
civilians in recent days.
</P>
<P>
The communique has demanded the unconditional release of Mr
Idiris Mohamed Osman, the head of the WFP office in Mogadishu,
who was abducted by unidentified gunmen in South Mogadishu two
days ago after performing his Friday prayers peacefully.
</P>
<P>
The Human Rights Center was bewildered that four abduction
cases in recent weeks were all victimized figures from the
minority or less armed clans in Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The center especially underlines the abduction cases of the
WFP employee, Osman, the French aid agency, ACF, staff member and
the brother of a well known businessman who all belong to the
minority clans in Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The communique signed by the two co-chairpersons of the human
rights center said they're concerned about the fate of Osman, the
WFP officer, whom they said was abducted for his clean
humanitarian efforts.
</P>
<P>
The human rights center said Osman has strongly opposed
corruption activities and illegal profit seeking by members from
the strong clans in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The center has called the faction leaders to stand firm
against such gross human rights violations.
</P>
<P>
Dr Ismail Jumale Human Rights Center has also accused the
faction leaders that the perpetrators of these human rights
violations are their armed supporters who repetitively commit
these crimes in the areas they control. Dr Ismail Jumale center
warned that the political assassinations, the rape, torture and
abduction in the absence of a national security institution will
not be tolerated as they will be registered and will be rewarded
one day.
</P>
<P>
The human rights center has appealed the political factions,
the traditional leaders and the intellectuals to collaborate in
preventing these crimes especially the human rights violations
against the poor defenseless minorities.
</P>
<P>
They have also called the people to work collectively towards
the restoration of the rule of law so as to secure the basic
rights of the people regardless of clans.
</P>
<P>
This is the first and strongest critics made by the local
human rights center against the faction leaders.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
