<HEADLINE> Iran Voices Support to Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi today voiced Tehran's support for Lebanon's resistance
against Israeli aggressions.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone conversation with his Lebanese counterpart Fares
Boueiz, Kharrazi said the Israeli regime has planned to create
a new crisis in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister said that the scheme can only
be interpreted in the context of its terrorist and expansionist
objectives against the Muslims and the Arabs.
</P>
<P>
He underlined the sovereignty and territorial integrity of
Lebanon and announced Iran's readiness to support the
international and regional efforts to stop the Israeli
aggressions.
</P>
<P>
According to a report carried by the official news agency
IRNA, Boueiz appreciated Iran's attention to the Middle East
problems and to the Lebanese people.
</P>
<P>
The telephone conversation came at a time when the
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright is touring the region
in a bid to revive the Meddle East peace process which has been
stalled since March. Iran has been a main supporter of the
Lebanese Hezbollah guerrillas who have been fighting against
Israeli occupation of south Lebanon in the last active battle
front of the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
