<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish-Georgian Military Accord Takes Effect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A military cooperation
agreement between Turkey and Georgia went into effect today, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Turkey and Georgia will exchange visits of
military delegations, cooperate with each other in troops training,
and dispatch observers for each other's maneuvers.
</P>
<P>
The military agreement between the two neighbors has a duration
of five years. Since the collapse of the former Soviet Union,
Turkey has turned its eye on developing closer relations with its
neighbors and especially central Asian countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
