<HEADLINE> Algeria Supports Syria to Liberate Occupied Lands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Algerian President
Liamine Zeroual said here today that Algeria supports Syria in
its fight to liberate its occupied lands.
</P>
<P>
During his second closed meeting today, Zeroual, who arrived
here Saturday, had underlined Algeria's support and solidarity
with Syria's struggle for the liberation of its occupied
territories, according to the Syrian presidential spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the Assad-Zeroual talks focussed on
developments in the region and events regarding the Middle East
peace process on account of the Israeli government stances. They
also discussed inter Arab action in defending Arab causes and Arab
dignity, the liberation of the occupied Arab territories and the
restoration of the usurped Arab rights.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added that the two Presidents were in agreement
that just and comprehensive peace could only be achieved on the
basis of the related international principles and decisions,
primarily the land-for-peace principle and Security Council
resolutions 242, 338 and 425.
</P>
<P>
The two Presidents, the spokesman indicated, spelled out the
importance and necessity of promoting bilateral relations in the
best interest of the two fraternal countries.
</P>
<P>
On his part, President Assad expressed hope that the Algerian
people would overcome their present difficulties so that Algeria
might pursue an Arab and international role commensurate with its
status and potentials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
