<HEADLINE> S. Africa Dispatches Planes to Search for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 14 (xinhua) -- The South African Air
Force today dispatched two aircrafts to Angola to help search for
people missing in a plane crash 200 km off Angola's western coast
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A German military aircraft carrying 24 people en route to
South Africa disappeared from radar screens at about 4 pm
Saturday, German defense officials said.
</P>
<P>
All 24 passengers, mainly german marines to take part in a
regatta with the South African Navy as part of its 75th
anniversary celebrations, were believed to be dead.
</P>
<P>
The German transport aircraft might have collided in mid-air
with an American transport aircraft, South African Press
Association quoted South African Air Force spokesman Laverne
Machine as reporting.
</P>
<P>
The German plane and a United States C141 transport plane
"both went off radar monitoring screens in the same vicinity
simultaneously", Machine said.
</P>
<P>
However, a U.S. airforce spokesman in Germany said he had no
information that any American aircraft might have been involved
in the Saturday air crash.  
</P>
</TEXT>
