<HEADLINE> Israeli PM Decides To Transfer More Funds To PNA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 14 (Xinhua)-- Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu decided today to release more funds to the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA), the Israeli Government Press
Office announced this evening.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu decided today to release 50 percent of balance of
funds whose transfer to PNA has until now been delayed, the
announcement said.
</P>
<P>
It said that Netanyahu took this decision as a goodwill gesture
in light of initial steps taken by PNA to fight against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Following the bombing blasts in Jerusalem on July 30, Israeli
side has frozen all tax revenues due to PNA along with a total
closure on the PNA controlled territories.
</P>
<P>
The exact total figure of frozen taxes has so far not been
made public by the Israeli side, but PNA put it at over 50
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Following bombing blasts on September 4 in Jerusalem, PNA has
speeded up its crack down on terrorism and so far over 100
militant suspects have been arrested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
