<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congress Hailed As Milestone in Party History (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Although the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) is still going on,
people have already got a common idea that the congress, the CPC's
last in the century, will have a far-reaching bearing on the
future of China. Hence, the congress is called "another important
milestone in the history of the CPC."
</P>
<P>
Since the congress declared open in September 12, quite a few
delegates to the congress have made two historical comparisons
which may help understand the significance of the congress.
</P>
<P>
First, the congress has established Deng Xiaoping Theory as the
guiding ideology, as the case of the Seventh National Party
Congress that established Mao Zedong Thought as the guiding
ideology.
</P>
<P>
This is another historic decision of the CPC, which marks
another leap in the Party's theoretical development. It is of
epoch-making significance.
</P>
<P>
Second, the exposition made in the report to the congress on
both the pattern of public ownership and the forms of its
realization is another emancipation of the mind and a theoretical
breakthrough. Earlier, the Party formulated the basic line with
economic development as the central task at the end of the 1970s,
and decided to begin establishing a socialist market economy in
1992.
</P>
<P>
The above-mentioned conclusion was drawn mainly from the report
Jiang Zemin delivered at the opening session of the congress.
</P>
<P>
As the congress has fulfilled the agenda of discussion of the
report, which together with the revision and adoption of the
report constitutes the main agenda and task of the congress,
people can draw conclusion on the outcome of the congress.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970915.0038 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congress Hailed As Milestone in Party History (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite the fact that the current congress differs from the
Seventh National Party Congress in terms of their respective
situations and tasks, the congress literally carries some
similarities with the congress in 1945 -- the last but the most
important congress in the period of democratic revolution, and
moreover, and with the two waves of emancipation of the mind
during the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
The Seventh CPC National Congress of 1945, in the wake of
Yan'an Rectification Movement, proceeded to break completely away
from the inclination of dogmatizing Marxism-Leninism.
</P>
<P>
The congress wrote Mao Zedong Thought into the Constitution of
the Party. Consequently, a sound theoretical foundation
unanimously agreed throughout the Party has been established, with
which the CPC successfully led the nation to triumph over the
Japanese invaders, and a few years later, founded the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The Third Plenum of the 11th CPC Central Committee, which was
convened in 1978, fundamentally shattered the argument of "two
whatevers" (the notion that after the death of Chairman Mao
Zedong, whatever policy decisions he had made must be firmly
upheld and whatever instructions he had given must be followed
unswervingly) on the basis of discussions over the criterion of
truth beginning in May that year.
</P>
<P>
The congress resolutely shifted the Party's central task to the
modernization drive, "a great turning point" that drew an end to
the two-year-long wavering after the Cultural Revolution.
</P>
<P>
Reforms and opening-up in the wake of that emancipation of the
mind in 1978 met another barrier in the early 1990s when it came
to the theoretical puzzle whether a market economy could be
introduced in a socialist countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970915.0039 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congress Hailed As Milestone in Party History (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the beginning of 1992, Deng Xiaoping, architect of China's
reform and opening policy, made talks in his south China tour, in
which he put forward the famous "three favorables" -- favorable to
promoting the growth of the productive forces in a socialist
society, increasing the overall strength of the socialist state
and raising the people's living standards. This gave rise to the
second major emancipation of the mind in the new period.
</P>
<P>
Later on in October of the same year, the third generation of
CPC leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core mapped out the major
strategic policy to establish the socialist market economy and to
accelerate the reform and opening-up, as well as the socialist
modernization drive. The following five years witnessed
significant successes.
</P>
<P>
After making the historical comparisons, the congress delegates
have drawn the following conclusion: Each major progress in the
history of the CPC resulted from the restoration of and adherence
to the Party's ideological line of "seeking truth from facts" and
the emancipation of the mind under the guidance of the line.
Especially in the last 20 years or so, along with each wave of
emancipation of the mind, there are inevitably breakthroughs in
reform and opening up and economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The delegates pointed out that although Jiang Zemin's report to
the 15th Party congress covers a wide range in terms of time and
space, the essence of Deng Xiaoping Theory -- "emancipating the
mind and seeking truth from facts" is embodied throughout the
report. It is where the hope and confidence of the current
conference lie. It is also why the conference has been highly
acclaimed by more than 2,000 delegates, including many veteran
revolutionaries.
</P>
<P>
After nearly 20 years of reform and opening up, China's reform
and development have come into a critical period with some
deep-rooted contradictions and problems waiting for solution. It
is understandable that people hold different views concerning the
national situation and development stage and some even are in
puzzles and have doubts about the orientation of the country's
further economic restructuring.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970915.0040 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 15:30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel's Deficit Falls in First Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Israel's current account
deficit reached some 2.3 billion U.S. dollars in the first half of
this year, Israeli Central Bureau of Statistics announced today.
</P>
<P>
This marked a reduction of 34.6 percent from nearly 3.7 billion
dollars registered in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The six-month figure comprised exports valued at 16.1 billion
dollars, imports worth 21.6 billion dollars and 3.1 billion
dollars in unilateral fund transfers to the country.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of 1996, exports stood at 14.7 billion
dollars, imports at 21.2 billion dollars and unilateral fund
transfers at 2.9 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The statistics indicate that imports of goods and services in
the January-June period grew by 380 million dollars from the same
period last year, because of an increase in expenditure on foreign
labor.
</P>
<P>
Within the overall imports volume of the first half of this
year, there was a decline in volume of the imported goods, but an
increase in imported services.
</P>
<P>
"The improvement is very important for the economy, because it
has reduced the danger of increased foreign debt above capacity,"
economist Professor Haim Ben-Shahar of Israeli Ben-Shahar
Associates commented on the deficit decline.
</P>
<P>
"But this was a result of reduced growth, not structural change
in the economy," warned the professor.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the fundamental solution for the current
account deficit is to cut government spending. "For every one
dollar reduced in government expenditure there will be at least a
one dollar reduction in the deficit under current conditions," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The bureau's data also shows that foreign debt increased by
some 2.2 billion dollars compared with a year ago, with a
1.1-billion-dollar rise in the economy's foreign-based assets.
</P>
<P>
Overall net foreign liabilities in the first six months of this
year totaled 20.3 billion dollars, which included assets of 28.6
billion dollars against a debt of 48.9 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment here reached 1.4 billion dollars in the
first six months of 1997, compared to 1.3 billion in the same
period last year. Meanwhile, Israeli overseas investments shrank
to 500 million dollars from 700 million dollars a year earlier.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970915.0041 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congress Hailed As Milestone in Party History (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The puzzles and doubts, if not removed, will obstruct the
reform process or even make the people lose their historical
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
That's why the 15th Party congress has held high the banner of
Deng Xiaoping Theory and further explained China's future
development. Undoubtedly, the move is of great significance.
</P>
<P>
Although the 14th Party congress has established the guiding
position in the Party for Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, the 15th congress has
decided to stipulate in the Party Constitution that the Party
takes Deng Xiaoping Theory as a guiding ideology to guide the 58
million Chinese Communist Party members. The move can guarantee
"holding high the banner." This explains why the congress
delegates call the current congress a meeting which "has made
historic contributions."
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Party Congress has further expounded the principle
of keeping public ownership in a dominant position and developing
diverse forms of ownership side by side, making it a basic
economic system in the primary stage of socialism.
</P>
<P>
Making clear that public ownership can take diversified forms,
the move has won a consensus among the congress delegates, who
pointed out the breakthroughs in theory will direct economic
restructuring, in the state sector in particular.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the conference will advance the entire
Party into a new realm ideologically and theoretically. After
breaking the ideological confines, China's reform will enter a new
period, bringing about a new economic and social development
stage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
