<HEADLINE> Worker-Delegates Meet Press </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Five hero- and model
worker-delegates to the current 15th National Party Congress, all
well-known across China, met several hundred Chinese and overseas
reporters here today.
</P>
<P>
All five delegates received wide coverage during the past few
years, four of whom have been elected into the presidium of the
current five-yearly congress.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for a national Party congress to
organize hero- and model worker-delegates to meet the press,
according to congress spokesman Xu Guangchun.
</P>
<P>
The Party always pays attention to delegates elected from among
the grass-roots units, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 494 model workers, experts and heroes from the
grass-roots units were elected delegates to the current Party
congress, accounting for 24.1% of the total number of delegates,
2.1 percent more than those to the last congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
