<HEADLINE> Beijing Reception Marks Mid-Autumn Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the
State Council and the United Front Work Department of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China jointly held a reception
here this evening to celebrate the traditional Mid-Autumn Festival,
which falls on tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
The reception was given in honor of consultants of the State Council
and members of the Central Research Institute of Culture and
History.
</P>
<P>
At the reception, Vice-Premier Li Lanqing made a speech, praising
them for their hard and efficient work in the past, especially in
the process of Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion of the Mid-Autumn Festival, Li said, "We are
eager to see an early reunion of the people across the Taiwan
Straits."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the only way out for Taiwan is the realization of
reunification of the Taiwan Island and the mainland. "Any attempt to
separate the Taiwan island from its motherland by the reactionary
forces on and outside the island will be unpopular and doomed to
failure.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the reception were Cheng Siyuan, vice-chairman
of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress; Luo
Gan, state councillor and secretary-general of the State Council;
and Yang Rudai and Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairmen of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
