<HEADLINE> Morocco quit of Davis Cup Tie in Tel Aviv </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Morocco has decided to quit a
Davis Cup tie with Israel in Tel Aviv for security reasons, a
national tennis federation spokesman said in Rabat on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Morocco had twice asked Israel for a change of location and
each time had been turned down, according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The requests came in the wake of two Jerusalem bombings, one of
which, on July 30, killed 17 people and injured 170.
</P>
<P>
The Davis Cup Euro/African Zone group one relegation tie was
due to be played in Tel Aviv from September 19 to 21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
