<HEADLINE> Martelli Quits Italy Davis Cup Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Marzio Martelli withdrew from
Italy's Davis Cup tennis squad after pulling his left hamstring on
Monday, just days before his side's semifinal clash with Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Martelli was replaced by Davide Sanguinetti, who ranks 95 in
the world but has never played in the competition before.
</P>
<P>
Sanguinetti is expected to compete in the singles, leaving
veteran partners Omar Camporese and Diego Nargiso to play
doubles. The other member of the Italian team is Renzo Furlan.
</P>
<P>
Italy, a dramatic quarter-finals winner over Spain, face last
year's beaten finalists in the Swedish city of Norrkoeping this
weekend.
</P>
<P>
The winners meet either Australia or the United States in the
final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
