<HEADLINE> Angolan-Cuban Commission to Meet in Luanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan-Cuban Mixed
Commission of Cooperation will meet here from today to Saturday
to review cooperation in all fields between the two
countries and discuss ways to strengthen cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Cuban Minister of Higher Education Fernando Alegrent arrived
here today to attend the ninth meeting of the mixed commission.
He told reporters upon his arrival that his country is willing to
expand cooperation relations with Angola.
</P>
<P>
He added that the close traditional friendly relations
between the two countries have laid a foundation for opening up
new areas of bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The mixed commission holds a meeting every two years. The last
meeting was held in Cuba in 1995. 
</P>
