<HEADLINE> Mir Computer System Breaks Down Anew </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The main computer system on
the Mir space station broke down again on Sunday, three cosmonauts
aboard were trying to fix it after the failure of the system, a
spokesman for ground control said today.
</P>
<P>
The latest incident on the Mir is the fourth computer
breakdown this year, the two Russians and one American on board
haven't been in danger. 
</P>
