<HEADLINE> Sino-German Building Technology Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of Sino-German
environmentally-friendly building technology opened today in
Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, the first of its kind in China, is sponsored by
two south German states -- Baden-Wurttemberg and Bavaria, which
are famous for their technology and achievements in environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will feature more than 30 lectures presented by
German experts.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning has also signed an environmental protection agreement
with the state of Baden-Wurttemberg, and fully expects to promote
bilateral cooperation in the sector.
</P>
<P>
Experts from Baden-Wurttemberg will help direct the local
environmental protection projects and promote technology transfers
between Germany and Liaoning.
</P>
<P>
Germany is one of Liaoning's major European trade partners,
with bilateral foreign trade in 1996 hitting 320 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Germany, the second largest European investor in Liaoning, has
funded nearly 100 enterprises in the province.
</P>
<P>
Similar exhibitions will be held in Suzhou in Jiangsu Province
and Qingdao in Shandong Province in east China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
