<HEADLINE> Congress Delegates Favor Industrialized Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Delegates to the on-going
15th national congress of the Communist Party of China agreed that
the emergence of industrialized agriculture in rural China is
another breakthrough after introducing the household contract
responsibility system with remuneration linked to output.
</P>
<P>
A unique feature of the industrialized agriculture is to take
market needs and efficiency as the sole purpose and serves the aim
of an intensive and commercialized production on a large scale
through integrating production, processing and sales.
</P>
<P>
Delegates attending the congress shared the view that the
Party Central Committee has endorsed the new creation of hundreds
of millions Chinese farmers, which has been proved an inevitable
trend of modern agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yanjiang, secretary of the Luozhuang Township Party
Committee in east China's Shandong Province, said the key to
achieving a big stride in rural economic development is to solve
the problem of low profit in farm production, develop agriculture
on a fairly large scale and promote the coordinated development
between industry and agriculture. The industrial management of
agriculture may meet these requirements, he added.
</P>
<P>
The industrial management of agriculture was based on the
development of rural industries, improvement of farmers'
management skill and the growth of a market-oriented economy, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Xia Houli, deputy head of the Dagangshan Township in east
China's Jiangxi Province, said practice has shown that the
industrial management of agriculture is an effective form of
developing a large-scale farm production on the basis of a
stabilized agriculture.
</P>
<P>
It has opened a new way for accelerating the growth of
agriculture through intensive production, he added.
</P>
<P>
Bian Ming from north China's Shanxi Province stressed the
importance of aiding key and rural enterprises which manufacturing
brand-name products in the course of promoting industrial
management of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shaokui, head of the Hebei Provincial Commission of
Science and Technology, said: "We should attach great importance
to the role of science and technology in promoting industrial
management of agriculture."
</P>
<P>
Key enterprises and scientific and technological departments
should use their advanced technology and other strong points to
contribute to the industrial management of agriculture.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
