<HEADLINE> Syria, Algeria Sign Accords to Promote Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Syria and Algeria signed
nine agreements here this morning to promote trade and economic
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
One of these agreements was on establishing a joint businessmen
council, another on preventing dual taxation and the others on
cooperation in trade, media, science and customs.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony was attended by Syrian Prime Minister
Mahmoud Zouebi, who met this morning with the Algerian delegation
that was accompanying President Liamine Zeroual on his two-day
visit to Syria.
</P>
<P>
Zouebi underlined the importance of developing cooperation
between the two countries in all fields.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume between Syria and Algeria amounted to 430
million Syrian lire (10 million U.S. dollars) in 1996, with 427.7
million Syrian lire (9.95 million dollars) being Syrian exports to
Algeria.
</P>
<P>
Syria's exports to Algeria include lentils, blood serum,
unmanufactured cotton and clothes.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Damascus, President Zeroual held talks with
his Syrian counterpart Hafez Al-Assad and other senior officials
on the new developments in the Middle East, especially the stalled
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Zeroual is due to leave Damascus later today for the Jordanian
capital of Amman for a visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
