<DOCNO> XIE19970915.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Declare Emergency When API Reaches 500 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Air Pollutant Index
(API) reading should reach 500 before any kind of emergency is
declared, Malaysian National Disaster Management Committee
Chairman Mohamed Rahmat said today.
</P>
<P>
The air quality throughout Malaysia is deteriorating due to the
worsening haze condition with today's API showing that the Gombak
area in Selangor State almost reached "hazardous" level with a
reading of 298.
</P>
<P>
Six other areas -- Nilai, Kuala Lumpur, Kajang, Klang, Petaling
Jaya and Melaka -- also reached a "very unhealthy" level, with
readings of between 200 and 300, an Environment Department
statement said today.
</P>
<P>
Mohamed, also information minister, told reporters after a
committee meeting that for the present it has been proposed that
open air burning be banned and factories directed to reduce their
smoke emissions.
</P>
<P>
He said it was also proposed at today's meeting that the number
of vehicles entering and leaving the worst haze affected areas be
restricted.
</P>
<P>
These proposals would be first submitted to the cabinet this
week for urgent implementation, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the committee proposed that police monitor open
burning activities in the Klang Valley where the capital city is
located. The committee also urged that cloud seeding be continued,
 earth works be reduced to check dust pollution and people dampen
their surroundings to prevent dust from going into the air.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is now enveloped by what has been described as its
worst-ever haze, a phenomenon blamed on forest fires in
Indonesia's Sumatra and Kalimantan regions.
</P>
<P>
According to Meteorological Department prediction, the haze
would continue for several more days.
</P>
<P>
Schools in the country need not close because of the haze but
they have been advised to reduce curricular activities, the
minister said, adding that only when the API exceeded the 400 mark
would schools be closed.
</P>
<P>
He said the committee advised those leaving their houses in
areas where the API reading has reached the 250 level to wear the
mouth mask.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad said
the government will declare a state of environmental emergency
only if the haze pollution hanging over the country reaches a
critical level.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
