<HEADLINE> Lhasa Hosts Tibet-Nepalese Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 China Tibet-Nepal
Trade Fair opened today in Lhasa, capital of southwest China's
Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The event, which has attracted 66 enterprises from the region
and Nepal, is expected to expand border trade for the region and
improve the local economic development. The fair offers some 100
products in 30 categories.
</P>
<P>
Instead of simply barter trade, the fair will focus on
bilateral cooperation for 10-odd projects, including the breeding
and processing edible funguses, and production of cashmere,
garments and nutrients.
</P>
<P>
Tibet's annual exports to Nepal account for more than 90
percent of the region's foreign trade, with the latter
participating in 28 joint and cooperative projects in the
former. Said projects involve total investments of over 103
million yuan. 
