<HEADLINE> India, Pakistan Begin Third Round of Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The crucial third round of
Indo-Pak foreign secretary level talks began here today to explore
options to resolve all outstanding bilateral issues, the Press
Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan Foreign Secretary Shamshad Ahmed, heading an
eight-member delegation, is scheduled to hold detailed parleys
from today to September 18 with his Indian counterpart, K.
Raghunath, against the backdrop of a summit between the prime
ministers of the two countries in New York on September 23.
</P>
<P>
During their second round of dialogue in Islamabad in June, the
two foreign secretaries decided to set up eight working groups on
all outstanding issues between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
But the two sides later differed on whether there would be a
working group on Kashmir which is regarded as a core issue by
Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
While Islamabad has contended that the decision covered the
establishment of a working group on Kashmir as on other issues,
India has argued that the two sides were only to work out a
mechanism for the purpose.
</P>
<P>
During the next few days, the two foreign secretaries are
expected to seek clarification over the contradicting
interpretations of the decision made in their second round of
talks.
</P>
<P>
They are also likely to lay the ground work for the keenly-
awaited meeting between Indian Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral
and his Pakistan counterpart, Nawaz Sharif, in New York where both
leaders are expected to address the 52nd session of the U.N.
General Assembly.  
</P>
