<HEADLINE> Iran Warns Against Turkey, Azerbaijan, Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister
Kamal Kharrazi today warned that the closer ties between Israel
and Iran's two neighbors Turkey and Azerbaijan have endangered
Iranian national security.
</P>
<P>
The minister told a press conference "We are naturally
considering the presence of the Zionist Regime in such countries
as Azerbaijan and Turkey and cooperation among them as against our
national security."
</P>
<P>
"We are not pleased at all with this. Naturally we are
watching these types of developments with serious concern,"
Kharrazi said.
</P>
<P>
He said "It is our natural right to be concerned about such
developments. We think that this is not in the interests of the
region that the Israeli regime would want to be present in this
region."
</P>
<P>
Early this month, the Iranian government strongly slammed the
Israel-U.S.-Turkey joint military maneuvers scheduled for
mid-November in the eastern Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi has said that such
cooperation is a source of crisis in the region and set Turkey
against the world of Islam.
</P>
<P>
"Iran considers Turkey a member of the Islamic community and
rejects its cooperation with the Zionist regime as detrimental to
the interests of the Muslims in the region," he added.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman condemned the scheduled joint maneuver between
Turkey and Israel and called it a threat to Arab states as
well as the whole region.
</P>
<P>
As for Azerbaijan, local observers noted Iran feels uneasy with
its intelligence cooperation with Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
