<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin's US Visit to Promote WTO Negotiations on China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The scheduled visit by
President Jiang Zemin to the United States later this year will
help promote economic and trade relations between China and the
United States, Sun Zhenyu, vice-minister of foreign trade and
economic cooperation, said here today.
</P>
<P>
The visit, a major event in the Sino-US relations, is to give
an impetus to the negotiations on China's entry into the World
Trade Organization (WTO), he said at a press conference held today
by the on-going 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China.
</P>
<P>
"Progress has been made in the Sino-US negotiations on China's
entry into the WTO. However, there still exist certain differences
between the two sides, mainly in the fields of service trade and
farm produce business," Sun said.
</P>
<P>
"China has made active efforts in this respect and signed
agreements with some signatories to the WTO on bilateral market
access," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope other WTO signatories will take a positive attitude
toward China's entry into the WTO," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Without China's participation, the WTO is an incomplete organ.
The WTO and its signatories will be the largest beneficiaries
after China is admitted into the body," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
