<HEADLINE> Ugandan Rebel Leader Flees to Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Joseph Kony, leader of the
rebel Lord's Resistance Army (LRA) of Uganda, has fled to Kenya,
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Dickens Canowira, an intelligence officer of LRA defecting to
the Ugandan government army on September 9, said Kony escaped
with hundreds of his subordinates.
</P>
<P>
Kony was expelled by the Sudan authorities, Canowira
disclosed, adding that there were some disagreements between the
rebel leader and the Sudan authorities.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Kony penetrated into northern Uganda
from southern Sudan with his 350 subordinates two weeks ago.
Earlier reports said the Uganda army cut the contacts between LRA
and local people in northern Ugandan districts and imposed a
heavy loss to the rebels.
</P>
<P>
LRA is a rebel group haunting in Uganda's northern districts
of Kitgum and Gulu and has bases in southern Sudan. 
</P>
