<HEADLINE> Zambia's Ruling Party Warns Against Dirty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Dirty campaigning for
positions of the Ruling Movement For Multi-Party Democracy (MMD)
has become rife in Lusaka, party chairman for elections Ackson
Sejani warned on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia today quoted Sejani as warning that all those
involved will be dealt with sternly.
</P>
<P>
Ackson Sejani called for a clean campaign where there will be
no underhand methods such as mud-slinging, name-calling and
intimidaion during the run-up to the party district elections,
which were originally scheduled for last week, have been postponed.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, MMD Lusaka District Chairman Harrson
Mukupa said the party will be destroyed if the forthcoming
elections are not free and fair.
</P>
<P>
He said the constituency officials should desist from
hand-picking candidates who are only loyal to one individual.
</P>
<P>
However, MMD Lusaka Provincial Chairman Christopher Chawinga,
who is aspiring for re-election, accused on Sunday Sejani of
leaning to one side by allowing MMD Deputy Treasurer Sylvia
Masebo to plant candidates of her own choice throughout the
consitituency.
</P>
<P>
But Masebo said, "I don't want to be drawn into discussing
cheap politics with a desperate man who became provincial
chairman by accident."
</P>
<P>
Sejani also said he is merely a political referee in the
elections and his only concern is to ensure the election
regulations are adhered to by all contestants.  
