<HEADLINE> Share Prices Slip Lower on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices slipped lower
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index lost 3.85 points to close at 1,932.1 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 118.91 million units, valued
at 230.02 million Singapore dollars (about 153.35 million US
dollars). Declines outnumbered advances by 232 to 115, while 263
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
CMTel 7k was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 8.68 million units. It was followed by BBRC which had
5.25 million shares traded. Ber Group was next with 4.69 million
shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 60 cents to finish at 33.8 Singapore
dollars. The Thai Prime Fund and the Venture warrant9907 increased
by 25 cents each to end at 6.5 US dollars and 5.6 Singapore
dollars respectively. The City Developments and the Singapore
Airlines gained 20 cents each to close at 10.2 and 8.35 Singapore
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation
(OCBC) Foreign was the biggest loser as it declined by 50 cents to
end at 11.2 Singapore dollars. The Development Bank of Singapore
(DBS) Foreign and the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign fell by
40 cents each to close at 15.6 and 12 Singapore dollars
respectively. Yeo HSS lost 35 cents to finish at five Singapore
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
