<HEADLINE> WB/IMF Annual Meetings' Press Center Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Journalists from all over
the world began to check in today for the World Bank/International
Monetary Fund Annual Meetings, and a press center especially
designed for the meetings was opened at the same time.
</P>
<P>
Over 2,000 journalists from various countries and regions are
expected to cover the WB/IMF meetings to be held from September 23
to 25 at the Extension of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center, as well as relevant seminars to be held before and during
the meetings.
</P>
<P>
Located on the 7th floor of the Extension, the press center has
over 520 workstations equipped with power outlets and telephones.
A number of typewriters and fax machines are also available in the
center.
</P>
<P>
Other facilities include a press lounge, six phone and radio
booths, a TV studio, three edit booths, and audio and video multi
boxes. Video walls and TV monitors will show the opening and
plenary sessions of the meetings.
</P>
<P>
The center also provides easy access to the Internet, for which
the computers in the center have been defaulted to allow users to
access all Websites, with the Hong Kong Monetary Authority's
Annual Meetings home page as the first point of browsing.
</P>
<P>
Being the first major international event that takes place in
Hong Kong after the handover on July 1, the meetings have aroused
intense interest among the press and more foreign reporters are
expected to fly in in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
The press center will remain open until September 26 when all
the programs related to the meetings conclude. 
</P>
</TEXT>
