<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Use More Foreign Funds, MOFTEC Vice-Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- China will continue to make
active, rational and effective use of foreign capital, encouraging
investment in industries to which China gives priorities,
Vice-Minister of foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Sun Zhenyu
said here today.
</P>
<P>
China will make big strides in the use of overseas investment
after the conclusion of the 15th National congress of the
Communist Party of China, Sun said at a press conference held by
the press center of the congress here today.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue to improve investment environment and raise
efficiency to make headway in the utilization of foreign funds,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the significance of the cut in tariff rates as of
October 1, which was announced yesterday, Sun said China will
reduce its average tariff rate from 23 percent to 17 percent. The
country will gradually dovetail its economic development with
internationally acknowledged practice.
</P>
<P>
On the non-tariff issue, he said, china has committed itself to
attaining the long-term target a decade ahead of the fixed date.
That is to say that China will call off all non-tariff measures by
the year 2010.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970915.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Use More Foreign Funds, MOFTEC Vice-Minister (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On foreign trade, Sun said the five years since 1992 were a
period in which China's foreign trade and economic cooperation
achieved its fastest progress.
</P>
<P>
In the period from 1992 to 1996, China's total foreign trade
value reached 1.168 trillion US dollars, a figure bigger than the
aggregate trade volume realized from the founding of new China in
1949 to 1991, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
The figure reflected an annual average growth rate of 16.4
percent which was above the growth rate of the national economy
and nearly eight percentage points higher than the annual growth
of world trade in the same period of the time, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sun predicted that China's import and export value will climb
to 400 billion dollars in the year 2000, which means that in the
four years between 1996 and 2000, China will offer a market worth
700 billion dollars and trade opportunities worth 1,400 billion
dollars to the world.
</P>
<P>
On promoting the bilateral trade between the both sides of the
Taiwan Straits, he said, investment from Taiwan constitutes a
fairly large proportion in overseas investment poured into China.
</P>
<P>
"We have worked out a series of measures to protect the
interests and rights of Taiwan investors. We hope the Taiwan
authorities will give up policies impeding investment on the
mainland of the motherland and do more practical work for the
reunification of China," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
