<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Driven Up By Dow Jones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
made strong gains to close higher today, driven by a rise in
banking and finance stocks, sparked by renewed interest rate
speculation and a rally on Wall Street on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Broker Richard Gregory said, the banking sector was pushed up
by a combination of an expected rate cut, a stronger bond market
and an announcement today by the National Australia Bank that it
would reinstitute its share buyback program.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed up 22.9 points at 2,662.9 after
the Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 81.79 points to 7,742.97 on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The interest-rate sensitive banking index finished on a high
note, up 91.9 points at 5,161.8.
</P>
<P>
Leading the banking stocks, National Australia Bank closed up
53.3 cents, Commonwealth Bank was 14 cents higher, ANZ Bank 16
cents grew while Westpac increased 16 cents.
</P>
<P>
The industrials' index was up a huge 50.9 points to 4,347.9,
while the all resources index went against the day's trend to
finish down 0.6 at 1,340.9.
</P>
<P>
The retail index also ended strongly, up 64.5 points to
3,383.0.
</P>
<P>
In the resources sector BHP rose six to 16.36 Australian
dollars, while Rio Tinto stocks fell two to 20.35 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 284.90 million shares traded worth 777.09
million Australian dollars (559.50 million US dollars), with rises
outnumbering falls 562 to 479.  
</P>
</TEXT>
