<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Higher in Thin trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar
finished slightly higher against the U.S. dollar in thin trading
today.
</P>
<P>
The local currency closed at 72.28 U.S. cents marginally higher
than previous close of 72.18.
</P>
<P>
Citibank senior dealer James Wallace said the currency market
was lethargic as a result of lack of local data and the absence of
Japanese traders due to a national holiday.
</P>
<P>
Wallace said the Australian dollar retained a slight upward
bias with support from local exporters and "it looks like it will
move upwards a little in the next few days."
</P>
<P>
The market remained swayed by sentiment dictating as easing
monetary policy stance with 59 percent of economists now expecting
a cut before the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished at 87.17 from 87.03 against the
Japanese yen and at 1.2825 from 1.2872 against the German mark.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
