<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Labor Market Remains Stable in Recent Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate and
the underemployment rate in Hong Kong for the June-August period
was 2.4 percent and 1.2 percent respectively, said the latest
labor force statistics released today by the Census and Statistics
Department.
</P>
<P>
Both figures remained unchanged compared with that for the
May-July period, during which the number of unemployed persons was
estimated at 69,000, and the number of underemployed persons at
37,800.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on these figures, a Government Secretariat spokesman
said that overall labor market conditions remained stable in
almost all the major sectors in recent months after further
tightening earlier in the year.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also pointed out that overall labor demand
remained on a strong uptrend amidst sustained growth in the
economy. In the three months ending July, total employment had a
further significant growth of 3.78 percent over a year earlier,
distinctly faster than that in total labor force, at 2.9 percent.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
