<HEADLINE> Zambian Immigration Officers Sacked for Extorting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- In an anti-corruption move,
Zambia Immigration Authorities have saked four Zambian
immigration officers in Kitwe in Copperbelt Province for
extorting money from an immigrant, Times of Zambia said today.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted immigration spokesman Royn Miyanda as
saying that the four officers have committed "indiscipline and
misconduct" by extorting mony from an immigrant.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted other informed sources as disclosing that
five were initially suspended for allegedly extorting money from a
west African immigrant.
</P>
<P>
They said after investigations and assesment of exculpatory
letters, one officer was reprieved and the rest were relieved of
their duties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
