<DOCNO> XIE19970915.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Famous Scientist's New Thought at Party Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Talking about the
opportunities, the latest developments in science and technology
are what should be taken advantage of by the Chinese, a
distinguished scientist told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"Rapid development in science and technology around the world
today has constantly brought about many new-born industries, which
in turn benefit the development of the entire society," Zhou
Guangzhao, a delegate to the current 15th National Party Congress, said
this today.
</P>
<P>
Zhou is currently the president of China Association of Science and
Technology.
</P>
<P>
This digitally-minded theoretic physicist let the reporters
look at his laptop computer,into which he had input pictures of
some of the world's most famed scientists and remarkable
inventions.
</P>
<P>
"Only those nations emphasizing science and technology, and
education while getting themselves fully prepared in terms of
knowledge and competent personnel are capable of seizing the
opportunities," said the ex-president of the Chinese Academy of
Sciences.
</P>
<P>
"The report laid a special emphasis on the role of science and
technology as the decisive factor behind economic development,"
Zhou said, stressing that efforts should be made to carry out this
guiding principle.
</P>
<P>
"In another word, we should give full play to our creativeness,
obtain the intellectual property right for industrial development
of the nation, cultivate a standardized and developed market
economy, and engage ourselves in the international competition,
association and division of labor, replace materials with digits,"
Zhou explained.
</P>
<P>
"If we lag behind modern technologies, we would be trapped in a
cul-de-sac," Zhou took E-mail as an example."But when you have
caught up with them, a complete readjusting of your former
knowledge structure is highly compulsory."
</P>
<P>
"For instance, now that the TV, computers and E-mail have been
integrated, is it still necessary for the country to keep so many
ministries?"
</P>
<P>
Zhou called for an attitude of seeking truth from the facts,
and emancipating the mind and base undertakings on the country's
actual conditions in this regard.
</P>
<P>
"Considering the reality in China," the scientist said, "China
should develop knowledge-intensive and energy- and raw
materials-saving products with high added-value, which is an
effective way out for a country like China with a large population
but insufficient resources."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
