<HEADLINE> Zambia's Opposition Leader Regrets Chitala's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- President of the opposition
Zambia Democratic Congress (ZDC) Dean Mungomba has regretted the
resignation of the party's General Secretary Derick Chitala but
said that his party is still doing fine.
</P>
<P>
Mungomba said here on Sunday that the ZDC Steering Committee
will soon meet to discuss the latest internal developments
including Chilata's resignation, Times of Zambia reported today.
</P>
<P>
"Chiltala's retirement is obviously regrettable but the party
is still doing well," he said.
</P>
<P>
Last week Chitala announced his resignation and said he was
retiring from politics.
</P>
<P>
Chitala has been a close friend and mentor of Mungomba.
</P>
<P>
Chitala was appointed First Deputy Finance Mminister in 1991
when the the ruling movement for the Multi-Party Democracy (MMD)
assumed office.
</P>
<P>
He was also the First Deputy MMD National Secretary until he
was expelled from the party with Mungomba in 1995. Chiltala and
Mungomba formed the ZDC in 1995, in which he served as secretary
general until the resignation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
