<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading British Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items in leading British newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The political truce over the death of Diana, Princess of
Wales, ended abruptly Sunday when Conservative leader Willian
Hague accused Tony Blair of making capital out of the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
The Financial Times:
</P>
<P>
