<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Chief of Mao's Home Village Praises Jiang's Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A delegate to the five-yearly
Party congress from late Chinese leader Mao Zedong's home village
said he was so excited and inspired that he clapped his hands on
more than 10 occasions when he listened to Jiang Zemin's report at
the opening session last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mao Yushi, secretary of the Chinese Communist Party Branch of
Shaoshan, in central China's Hunan Province, said he was so eager
to tell his fellow villagers about Jiang's report that he called
them through mobile phone minutes after the conclusion of the
opening session and before leaving the venue, the Great Hall of
the People.
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Jiang Zemin has given a terrific report," shouted Mao
to his phone. "I joined other delegates in clapping hands more
than 10 times when listening to his report. I still feel pains in
my palms," said Mao Yushi.
</P>
<P>
However, when he was about leaving for the hotel to tell his
fellow villagers more of the congress, he was stopped by overseas
reporters on the staircases outside the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
When he was asked to compare Mao Zedong with Deng Xiaoping, he
said, "Both Mao and Deng advocated seeking truth from facts and
serving the people. They were identical on this point. Of course,
they were in different times and therefore faced with different
tasks."
</P>
<P>
In the order of seniority in the Mao clan, Mao Yushi, 51, is
Mao Zedong's junior by one generation. Around 70 percent of the
1,200 people in his village have the surname of "Mao."
</P>
<P>
"Since I have come for the Party congress, I must speak for
farmers, especially on the rural policy and rural economic
development," the village Party head said.
</P>
<P>
"We farmers can witness the solid changes brought by Deng
Xiaoping Theory," said he, adding there was no decent houses in
Shaoshan Village in the early 1980s. By now, all the villagers
have built their new houses.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the average per capita annual income in his village
reached 5,200 yuan, some four times the national figure. All
families in the village have bought television sets, refrigerators
and washing machines. Some of them have bought air-conditioners
and stereos and six farmers have their own cars, he said.
</P>
<P>
The village Party secretary is relieved that the report by
Jiang Zemin has taken agriculture as the center of economic
development. Still, Mao put forward some suggestions on promoting
agriculture by science and technology, the building of grassroots
organizations and the public security issue.
</P>
<P>
Shaoshan Village has two Party branches with over 60 Party
members. Some 30 more villagers have applied for the Party
membership. July 1, the birthday of the CPC, September 9, the day
when Mao Zedong passed away, and December 26, the birthday of Mao
Zedong, have become regular commemoration days for the village
Party members, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
