<HEADLINE> China Expanding Foreign Contacts In Biology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and foreign
biologists and pharmaceutical company representatives gathered in
Beijing today for the start of a three-day symposium on
co-operation in the field of biology.
</P>
<P>
It is sponsored by the Ministry of Health and attracted 22
multinational pharmaceutical companies from the US, Japan,
Germany, Britain, Denmark, and elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
China has more than 440 companies involved in biological
production, but only a small number in high-tech products like
gene engineering.
</P>
<P>
A State Science and Technology Commission official says that
China expects to learn from other countries about developing
biological products.
</P>
<P>
During the Ninth Five-Year Plan period, China will focus on new
pharmaceuticals, vaccines, and genetic medical therapy, in
addition to high-yield, high-quality seed production. It has
increased co-operation with other countries. The Sino-European
biological technology center, established in 1991, has had 41
co-operative projects.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, China has developed legal protection for
patented foreign biological technology and administrative
protection of imported pharmaceuticals. It has signed agreements
with 19 countries, including the US, Japan, the European Union
states, and some other developed countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
