<HEADLINE> Foreign Exchange Reserves Increase in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Foreign exchange reserves at
the state-owned Bank of Uganda has grown from 479.7 million U.S.
Dollars in June last year to 625.59 million Dollars at the end of
June this year.
</P>
<P>
Local daily "The Monitor" today quoted a high profile
government working document as saying that the present level of
reserves represents about five months of import cover.
</P>
<P>
In another development, a similar rise in gold exports
persists even now with a dramatic 106.7 million Dollars bagged by
end of June, over 100 percent rise from 35.15 million Dollars
posted by end of last financial year.
</P>
<P>
According to the document, at present Uganda's domestic debt
stands at 75 billion Shillings (about 75 million U.S. Dollars) while
its external debt is 3.5 billion Dollars. 
</P>
