<HEADLINE> Israel Lifts Internal Closure on Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli Army announced
today that the internal closure on Palestinian areas in the West
Bank and Gaza Strip was lifted at 5 o'clock this morning.
</P>
<P>
An army spokesman said that Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak
Mordechai and Army Chief of Staff Ammon Shahak have approved the
easing of the internal closure. However, he added that the
general closure on the territories remains in force.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 2,300 merchants, medical personnel, clergy and
staff of international organizations from the Palestinian-ruled
areas were permitted to enter Israel.
</P>
<P>
Following the bombing attack in Jerusalem on September 4, which
killed seven people and wounded 190 others, Israel re-imposed the
total closure on the West Bank and Gaza Strip and demanded all
Palestinian workers inside Israel return to their homes.
</P>
<P>
Internal closure was also ordered on villages and towns under
Palestinian control and Palestinians were barred from entering
industrial zones in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Israel's decision to ease internal closure was a gesture of
good will in view of the initial steps taken by the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) in the anti-terror war after United
States Secretary of State Madeleine Albright's three-day visit to
Israel and Palestinian-ruled areas last week.
</P>
<P>
Israeli officials have described Albright's talks with the PNA
as a qualified success, saying that she convinced the PNA that
it must wage an all-out war against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The PNA has arrested 120 militants in the wake of Albright's
visit. Palestinian and Israeli security officials also met
last weekend in what both sides termed a productive session.
The PNA later said that it would continue its fight against
terrorism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
