links with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa visited South Africa on
August 24-26, when he signed with his South African counterpart
Alfred Nzo several agreements of cooperation in tourism, science
and technology, art and culture, avoidance of double taxation and
prevention of fiscal evasion, and air services.
</P>
<P>
The trade between Egypt and South Africa last year ran under
100 million U.S. dollars. Egypt is South Africa's third biggest
trading partner in the Arab world and second largest supplier in
Africa. 
