<HEADLINE> Increasing Teachers' Living Quarters In South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Staff members at four
universities and colleges in China's Guangdong Province received a
special gift from the provincial government on Teachers' Day,
which fell on September 10.
</P>
<P>
A 30-story apartment building with 60,000 sq.m. of floor space
was presented by the provincial government on September 10, to
provide more space for some 400 teachers.
</P>
<P>
The 120-million-yuan project is part of the government's effort
to improve the standard of living of more than 42,300 college
teachers. It has allocated 70 million yuan annually since 1993 for
construction of apartments for university teachers.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, floor space of university teachers in
the province averaged 45.1 square meters per person.
</P>
<P>
The province has now set a goal for the rest of the century of
seeing that each professor has no less than 90 sq.m., and that an
associate professor has no less than 80 sq.m.
</P>
<P>
There are some 160,000 sq.m. of residential buildings for
university teachers now under construction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
