<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diary of Party Congress Delegates (Sept. 15) - 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- (At Xinhua's request, some
delegates to the current 15th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) write what they see, discuss and think during
the congress in diary form, which we think will provide outsiders
with some information about this major event. The following diary,
the fifth of its kind, was written by Professor Li Wenhai,
president of People's University of China. -- Ed.)
</P>
<P>
The report delivered by Jiang Zemin at the opening session of
the congress made an incisive exposition over the cause of
building socialist culture with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin stressed that a socialist culture with Chinese
characteristics is a major force in uniting and inspiring the
people, and an important indicator of our overall national
strength.
</P>
<P>
He further urged that the whole Party fully understand that
cultural advancement is essential and urgent because it plays a
great role in developing the cause of socialism and rejuvenating
the nation.
</P>
<P>
The reforms and development of culture, like rivers and forests,
have origins and roots. Then, what are the origins and the root
of socialist culture with Chinese characteristics?
</P>
<P>
The report clearly answered that "This culture originated from
the 5,000-year-old civilization of the Chinese nation and is
deeply rooted in our endeavor to build socialism with Chinese
characteristics" and "it has distinctive features of the time."
</P>
<P>
China is a country with a long history and a culture of long
standing and the 5,000-year-long civilization of the Chinese
nation is an inexhaustible cultural treasury.
</P>
</TEXT>
