<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Responsibility System For Grassland to be fully implemented </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- China's herdsmen are expected
to work under a contract responsibility system by the end of this
century, according to an agriculture official.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yanxi, vice-minister of agriculture, told a meeting here
recently that he approves of the results of the system in
improving animal husbandry and protecting the ecology of the
nation's vast grasslands.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, about 1.7 billion mu (113 million
hectares) of grassland, or 35.6 percent of China's usable
grassland, were being cared for under contract by herdsmen.
</P>
<P>
Most of China's pasture is located in frontier areas
inhabited by ethnic minority groups who used to live a migrant
life.
</P>
<P>
The full implementation of the contract responsibility system
is of strategic importance to developing frontier areas and to
improving herdsmen's life, Zhang said. Statistics show that some
16.74 million people in the pasture areas still live below the
official poverty line, accounting for about 30 percent of the
country's total.
</P>
<P>
"The contract responsibility system has also proved to be
effective in preventing the grassland ecology from deteriorating,"
Zhang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
