<HEADLINE> Iranian Ali Daei Named Asia's Best Player of August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Ali Daei of Iran was
honored as the Asian Player of the Month in August, the Asian
Football Confederation said in a statement here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Daei who joined Arminia Bielefeld in the Bundesliga recently,
has made an immediate impact on the German soccer scene "with two
goals in the first four games of one of the toughest leagues in
Europe to further his claim as Asia's number one hitman", said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Jubilo Iwata was named the best team for August, the
only team to be level on points at the top of the table against
defending champions Kashima Antlers.
</P>
<P>
Jubilo has made the feat although Brazilian coach Luiz Felipe
Scolari had left the team and former Italian World Cup star
Salvatore Schillachi was about to leave.
</P>
<P>
Coach of the month was Kim Ho, the man in charge of South
Korea's league team Suwon Bluewings.
</P>
<P>
It was Kim's guidance that played a major role in Suwon's race
to the top of the Korean league, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The awards are given monthly by a panel of sports writers,
soccer officials and others. 
</P>
