<HEADLINE> 14 Electrocuted in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- At least 14 people were
electrocuted in Bihar, India, on Sunday night when they came into
contact with a live, high-tension wire passing near a building,
the Times of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
The victims, mostly boys in the age between 15 and 25, were
sitting on the roof of the building, watching a dancing program in
the vicinity of a temple.
</P>
<P>
They were in an inebriated state when one of them came into
contact with the live wire passing close over his head. The
current spread among others through contact.
</P>
<P>
Five persons, who survived as they immediately jumped to the
ground, are being treated for severe burns at a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
While unconfirmed reports said the death toll was at least 30,
the local police put the figure at 14. A magisterial inquiry has
been ordered into the incident.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
