<HEADLINE> Chinese Duo Wins Springboard Synchronized Diving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Zhang Jing and
Shi Lei collected 304.05 points to take the women's three-meter
springboard synchronized title as the 10th World Cup diving
competition concluded here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
This was the sixth gold medal won by China in the five-day
competition.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese duo scored their winning points of 304.05, beating
German Dorte Lindner and Simona Koch to second with 279.48.
</P>
<P>
Maria Dolores Saez de Ibarra and Julia Maria Cruz gave Spain
its first medal of the competition with a bronze after finishing
with 268.20 points.
</P>
<P>
Dimitry Sautin of Russia took his second gold medal by winning
the 10-meter platform, the same event he won in the 1996 Olympics.
</P>
<P>
It was Sautin who awarded Russia two gold medals as he also
triumphed in the 3-meter springboard on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the platform, Sautin finished with 509.37 points, well ahead
of runner-up Fernando Platas of Mexico who had 480.03.
</P>
<P>
Xu Hao of China was third with 476.40. American Mark Ruiz and
David Pichler tailed in the six-man finals.
</P>
<P>
China finished atop the medal table with six golds, three
silvers and five bronzes. Russia was in a distant second place
with two golds and one silver while Canada finished third with two
golds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
