<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan President Pays Visit to Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President
Chandrika Kumaratunga left here today for Malaysia on a four-day
visit.
</P>
<P>
This is the first official visit to Malaysia by a top Sri
Lankan leader since the visit by former prime minister Dudley
Senanayake in 1967.
</P>
<P>
The president is accompanied by Foreign Minister Lakshman
Kadirgamar.
</P>
<P>
The visit is aimed at promoting economic ties between the two
countries, close sources said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's exports to Malaysia increased sharply from 6
million U.S. dollars in 1994 to about 27 million dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
During her stay in Malaysia, President Kumaratunga will hold
talks with Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will sign several agreements on a number of
projects concerning infrastructure development, airport expansion
and technological cooperation.  
</P>
