<HEADLINE> Major News Items In Leading S. African Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items in leading South African newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
The Citizen
</P>
<P>
-- The powerful Congress of South African Trade Unions will
hold a strategic meeting in Johannesburg tomorrow, in which
delegates are to discuss the tripartite alliance between the
ruling African National Congress, the South African Communist
Party and the labor group.
</P>
<P>
-- The National Party, the biggest white party in South
Africa, yesterday criticized Correctional Services Minister Sipo
Mzimela's proposal to turn ships into prisons.
</P>
