<HEADLINE> SKorea Press: China to Further Develop Market Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 15 (Xinhua) -- China will further develop
market economy, a principle reiterated by Chinese President Jiang
Zemin at the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), a newspaper editorial said today.
</P>
<P>
Outlining China's blueprint for the 21st century, Jiang
stressed that China's economic development is still at the primary
stage of socialism.
</P>
<P>
This indicates that China is determined to further develop
market economy and make more active efforts to push forward its
reforms, said the editorial carried by the Korean Daily News today.
</P>
<P>
Unlike some other emerging countries in Asia, which are still
struggling to get out of economic difficulties, China's economy
has grown steadily into a strong force, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
However, the editorial added, the remarkable changes in China
did not come overnight. They are a result of unyielding efforts of
the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
What is going on in China will leave a significant impact in
this region, the editorial said. 
</P>
