<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Tamil Rebels Set Fire to Bungalows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels
stormed and set ablaze three bungalows in the Yala National Park
in the south of the country Saturday night, according to reports
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
About 30 rebels stormed the three bungalows, hijacked a van
with its driver and set fire to the buildings before withdrawing
into the jungles. The driver later escaped.
</P>
<P>
The attackers were dressed in army-type uniforms when they
launched the attack.
</P>
<P>
A combined team of police and armed forces combed the jungles
Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier attack on the park, the Tamil Tigers set fire to
boats of local fishermen.  
