<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Beltway Railroad Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's new beltway railroad
linking the capital of Yangon and Mandalay, Myanmar's second
largest city in the north, has opened with the newly-finished
Aunglan-Pyay section going into service.
</P>
<P>
The 1,388-kilometer-long Yangon-Mandalay railroad, which lies
in the west of the Bago mountain range, is another north-south
main route running parallel with the old Yangon-Mandalay railroad
in the east of the mountain range.
</P>
<P>
Today's the New Light of Myanmar quoted General Maung Aye,
vice-chairman of Myanmar's ruling State Law and Order Restoration
Council as saying at Sunday's inaugural ceremony that Myanmar has
built 1,243 kilometers of new railroads in the whole country since
1988, when the country had 3,162 kilometers of railroads.
</P>
