<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Private Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The private sector in east
China's Anhui Province has emerged as a driving force in local
economic development and has contributed some 11 percent of the
province's industrial and commercial taxes.
</P>
<P>
The province's 1.11 million family businesses and 17,600
private enterprises in place by the end of June employed some 2.7
million employees, said Wang Shengbang, director of the provincial
Administration Bureau for Industry and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
The sector accounts for 70 percent of the province's
commercial, service and catering outlets. The private sector has
also helped to promote reform of state lumber enterprises by
contracting, leasing or purchasing small- to medium-sized state or
collective enterprises and employing a large number of redundant
workers.
</P>
<P>
The ever increasing number of technicians, college graduates
and retired professionals has greatly enhanced the sector's level
of competition.
</P>
<P>
Anhui is currently home to 14 of the nations top 500 private
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
A number of private businesses have entered the agricultural
sector, and an increasing number are venturing into the production
and export sectors. according to Wang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
