<HEADLINE> Crime-stoppers Awarded In East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 15 (Xinhua) -- A migrant jobber has been
honored by east China's Fujian Province for his courage in
fighting against an offender.
</P>
<P>
Chen De, from southwest China's Sichuan Province, caught a
thief in the act of robbing the home of Chen's neighbor, and
overpowered the crook after a fierce fight.
</P>
<P>
The thief left eight knife-wounds on Chen's head and face.
</P>
<P>
Chen and 36 other heroes were awarded at a ceremony by the
Provincial Public Security Volunteers Foundation last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The three-year-old foundation, with a capital of 14.6 million
yuan (about 1.8 million US dollars), has rewarded 159
crime-stoppers with a total award of 1.76 million yuan (about 0.22
million dollars).
</P>
<P>
"More courageous people were awarded this time, and that means
a healthy attitude against crime prevails here," said the
foundation's director.  
</P>
