<HEADLINE> Rosskopf Wins European Table Tennis Masters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- German Jorg Rosskopf outwitted
Zoran Primorac of Croatia in straight sets to take the title of
the seventh European Table Tennis Masters on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old German, Olympic bronze medalist, notched up his
third title of the tournament by beating Primorac 21-16, 21-15 and
21-15, following his victories in 1993 and 1995.
</P>
<P>
Rosskopf enjoyed his upperhands from the very beginning and
dominated the final competition till his last winning strike.
</P>
<P>
En route to taking his third crown, Rosskopf eliminated former
European champion Jean Michel Saive of Belgium 22-20, 21-18, 18-21
and 21-14 in the quarters and Swedish Jan Ove Waldner in the
semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Against Waldner, Rosskopf took the first two sets 21-16, 21-15
before the Swedish veteran rallied back to level the score 2-2 by
winning the following sets 21-15 and 21-19.
</P>
<P>
In the decider, Rosskopf regained his top form and surged
towards his victory 21-11 in a hurry while Waldner stumbled time
and again. 
</P>
</TEXT>
