<HEADLINE> Beijing to Hike Waste Disposal Quotient </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital plans to
increase the disposal rate of the city's garbage to 60 percent by
the turn of the century, from some 40 percent at present.
</P>
<P>
As an important step to reach the goal, Beijing is to introduce
rubbish sorting in some public places and more institutions and
enterprises, according to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
The city that produces about 13,000 tons of rubbish daily began
sorting rubbish last year into different categories so that glass,
plastics, metal, paper and others can be recycled.
</P>
<P>
However, local residents throw all kinds of garbage, of which
at least 30 to 40 percent can be recycled, in one place, making
recycling hard, the report said.
</P>
<P>
If all the rubbish that can be recycled is collected
separately, the city's rubbish can be reduced by more than 30
percent, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Environment Protection Bureau has asked producers
of plastic food container to recycle the discarded containers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city has decided to build more dumps with
furnaces for burning garbage in suburban areas.
</P>
<P>
For example, three furnaces which are being built in Changping
County are expected to burn 500 tons of rubbish each day, the
daily amount of garbage produced by Changping and its surrounding
areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
