</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- South African deputy president Thabo Mbeki and
parliament member Winnie Madikizela-Mandela have been nominated as
the president and deputy president of the ruling African National
Congress (ANC).
</P>
<P>
The nominations were made Sunday by the national executive
committee of the ANC woman's league following a meeting held in
Johannesburg.
</P>
<P>
ANC president Nelson Mandela, also president of South Africa,
has announced that he will retire from the party's presidency at
the ANC's national congress to be held in
December. (S. Africa-nominations)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright here
Sunday's evening admitted only small steps were accomplished
during her week-long trip to the region with the
Israeli-Palestinian peace negotiations to be reactivated at double
levels.
</P>
<P>
Big steps were needed, but small steps were better than no
steps, Albright emphasized during a joint press conference with
Jordan's King Hussein. She said Israel and Palestine agreed to
start top leader-level talks in Washington and minister-level
talks in New York at the end of this month. (Jordan-US-Albright)
</P>
