<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dinosaur Fossils Unearthed in Hubei Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese paleontologists
have announced the discovery of rare dinosaur fossils dating
back some 90 million years in central China's Hubei province.
</P>
<P>
The fossils represent three dinosaurs from the "Bird-Foot
Family", according to paleontologists from the Institute of
Vertebrate Paleontology and Paleoanthropology under the Chinese
Academy of Sciences. The body of the largest dinosaur measures
some six meters in length and the smallest some two meters.
</P>
<P>
These fossils were unearthed on July 25 by farmers
constructing water conservancy facilities in a village in Yun
County. Local residents reported the find to officials and
scientists who later concluded the discovery of fossilized
skeletons of three dinosaurs.
</P>
<P>
The find will greatly benefit studies of the geography and
climate in the mid-Cretaceous Period, according to
scientists. They also noted that the discovery will provide
valuable clues to the extinction of the giant creatures some 65
million years ago.
</P>
<P>
Paleontologists pointed out that the fossils indicated that the
dinosaurs suffered from various diseases which might have lead
to their death.
</P>
<P>
Archeologists perviously unearthed the teeth of primitive man
and fossilized dinosaur eggs in the same region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970915.0238 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil, Germany Break Into Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Brazil beat Argentina 2-1 on
Sunday to secure the first semi-final berth of the Under-17 Soccer
World Championship before goalkeeper Roman Weidenfeller palmed off
four penalty kicks to see Germany survive.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, runner-up at the 1995 U-17 World Championship,
unleashed enoumous attacks against the strong Argentine defense in
the first quarter-final match between the group C winner and group
D's runner-up in the Mediterranean city of Alexandria.
</P>
<P>
The first half was on the way to be ended goalless until Fabio
Pinto scored in the 45th minutue. Pinto swung in the header from
the rim of the penalty box.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's second goal came seven minutes before time, and it was
again from Pinto who scored his right kick with speed and force.
</P>
<P>
In another quarter-final match in Cairo, German goalie did
credit to his team with great saves in the penalty shoot-out, and
turned the game into a hilarious win of 4-3.
</P>
<P>
Both Germany and Mali had been intent on putting up a strong
defense since the kickoff. In the second half, the Malis gradually
dominated the court but they missed the chances.
</P>
<P>
The 90-minute property and 30-minute extra time ended in a
goaless draw. In the penalties, Weidenfeller, in a perfect show of
confidence and skill, pushed out four penalty kicks, while his
Mali counterpart Mamadou Thiam managed to sweep out only three.
</P>
<P>
After a recess on September 16 and 17, Brazil will play Germany
in the Suez Canal city of Ismailia.
</P>
<P>
Monday will see the fights between Ghana and Oman and between
Spain and Egypt for the other two slots in the semi-finals.
</P>
</TEXT>
