<HEADLINE> Chinese Clock Manufacturer Wins ISO Accreditation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Yantai Wood Clock Factory
in east China's Shandong province was recently granted
international ISO 9001 accreditation for its high quality design,
production and services.
</P>
<P>
The factory, the nation's timepiece manufacturers to win the
accreditation, expects that the certification will help increase
its share in the overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
The 80-year old factory, one of the country's leading clock
makers, produces more than 300 varieties of products ranging from
mechanical, wood veneer and artistic clocks.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 the factory's exports valued at 50 million yuan (6
million U.S. dollars), up 17 percent on the previous year and
accounting for over half of the national exports.
</P>
<P>
The factory registered 60 million yuan in domestic sales last
year and held 40 percent of the domestic clock market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
