<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Cultural Activities Prosper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 15 (Xinhua) -- Cultural activities in
northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region have been
prospering over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
A local culture official pointed out that ethnic groups in the
region have created numerous songs and dances such as "Rainbow
Over Tianshan Mountains" which won three national arts titles in
1994.
</P>
<P>
The regional government has allocated over four million yuan to
over 100 cultural centers, cinemas, and libraries in rural areas
to offer local residents access to wide-ranging activities,
according to one local official, He added the that some 29 famous
historical relics have been renovated and placed under state and
provincial protection in the past five years alone.
</P>
<P>
The official noted: "Xinjiang formed an art troupe to stage
traditional ethnic culture and arts performances in 1992". Thus
far the troupe has staged 12 performances of ethnic songs
and dances, local opera, and music from China and 20 countries and
regions throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, local cultural departments have published
a wide range of works and audio-visual pieces related to
traditional culture and art forms.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang has has sent 200-odd art troupes to some 20 countries,
and has hosted over overseas 3,000 artists as part of cultural
exchange programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
