<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dutch Take European Volleyball Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 14 (Xinhua) -- They spiked harder, passed
smarter and blocked tighter when the Dutch added the European
volleyball championship to their Olympic title on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Yet the championship hosts encountered real resistance from
opposite the net for the first time in the seven matches they
played at Eindhoven en route to winning the continental honor.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia at one time gave the Dutch side some tentalizing
headaches with solid blocks and smart passes. The Dutch spikers
finally proved their one-upmanship in the end with a 15-11, 10-15,
15-10, 15-9 victory.
</P>
<P>
Dutch playmaker Peter Blange and blocker Reinder Nommudor
turned out to be the heroes of the match. They often doubled up
their key roles by blocking up the net and digging to save at rear
court to unleash their versatility.
</P>
<P>
Blange and Nommudor paired off to successfully block several of
the Yugoslav killer smashes in the third set to curb the
counterattack from across the net.
</P>
<P>
Trailing 0-2 into the fourth set, Nommudor shot five cunning
serves in a row to disturb the playing rhythm of the Yugoslav
spikers before the score was reversed to 5-2 in favor of the Dutch
team.
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's semi-finals, the Netherlands blanked world league
titlists Italy 15-9, 15-6, 15-13 while Yugoslavia whitewashed
France 15-6, 17-15, 15-11.
</P>
<P>
Italy tucked home a bronze medal from the week-long tournament
by defeating France three sets to one in the day's third-place
playoff.
</P>
<P>
Russia downed the Czech Republic 3-0 to finish fifth while the
seventh position went to Ukraine that ran away with a 3-0 triumph
from Slovakia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
